abstract: Gautam Bhatia article on virtues of traditional Indian buildings; pokes fun at intelligence e-building constructed in suburb of Delhi for leading software company (M)
snippet: Gautam Bhatia article on virtues of traditional Indian buildings; pokes fun at intelligence e-building constructed in suburb of Delhi for leading software company (M)
lead_paragraph: One evening a few years ago, I found myself on the road that heads south out of Delhi, in the city's fastest-developing suburb: Qutab Enclave. The area along the road was one big construction site. Many new structures sat between piles of rubble, and workers milled around concrete mixers on brown hot ground, half dug, half built. Pigs and stray dogs strolled near new plate-glass outlets for Reebok, Benetton and Levi's.
